lowing support:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Consulting on Effective Messaging and Programming for Young People</li>\r\n	<li>Creation & Maintenance of Youth Advisory Councils</li>\r\n	<li>Strategy for List Building & Member Acquisition</li>\r\n	<li>Building Programs & Tech for Scale</li>\r\n	<li>Creating Brand Ambassadors</li>\r\n	<li>Training on Managing Millennials in Your Office</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:4:\"icon\";s:14:\"user-interface\";s:10:\"customicon\";s:86:\"http://www.tmiagency.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Services_engaging-young-people.png\";}i:4;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:19:\"MOBILE/SMS STRATEGY\";s:11:\"description\";s:1155:\"<p>(2) There has been a 27% decline in email usage among those ages 12-34 over the past year, and an average email open rate is only 22%. When it comes to texting, on the other hand, messages have a 99% open rate (basically the holy grail of all open rates). With the average mobile phone user sending/receiving 1,245 text messages every month and the average teen sending 3,339 texts, SMS communication is an undeniably powerful tool. </p> \r\n\r\n<p>In 2011, DoSomething.org pivoted to focus on text messaging and the results were amazing—texting members proved to be 11x more effective than emailing them. DoSomething.org’s mobile subscriber list recently surpassed 1.1 million people, and we also created a proprietary mobile gaming product to garner higher engagement levels. Through mobile strategy, TMI can help your brand make the same pivot to mobile, thereby engaging people on the platform they prefer most. Services include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Integrating Mobile/SMS Outreach into Your Programs</li>\r\n	<li>Mobile Gaming</li>\r\n	<li>Mobile Platform Setup (via Mobile Commons)\r\n	<li>Strategy for List Building & Member Acquisition</li></li>\r\n</ul>\";s:4:\"icon\";s:14:\"user-interface\";s:10:\"customicon\";s:71:\"http://www.tmiagency.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Services_mobile.png\";}i:6;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:32:\"BRAND STRATEGY & CAUSE MARKETING\";s:11:\"description\";s:993:\"<p>(3) DoSomething.org has successfully built a brand that is recognizable and well-known. We know that a brand includes so much more than just your logo—you need audience-appropriate messaging and tone, creative design, catchy copy, an obvious value-add proposition, and much more. Having a specific cause linked to your brand is also extremely important today—especially to young people who are choosing their brand allegiances. </p>\r\n\r\n<p>DoSomething.org is THE company that youth brands look to for cause marketing campaigns, with past partners including: Walmart, HP, AT&T, JPMC, Microsoft, American Express, and Google. TMI will open your eyes to what young people think of your brand now, help you improve it, and help you rock your next CSR or cause marketing initiative. Services include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Brand Audit</li>\r\n	<li>Cause Marketing Strategy</li>\r\n	<li>CSR Strategy</li>\r\n	<li>Rebranding</li>\r\n	<li>Website Design & Build</li>\r\n	<li>Measuring Impact & ROI</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:4:\"icon\";s:14:\"user-interface\";s:10:\"customicon\";s:70:\"http://www.tmiagency.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Services_brand.png\";}i:7;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:12:\"SOCIAL MEDIA\";s:11:\"description\";s:589:\"<p>(4) DoSomething.org is one of the top 100 Most Influential Brands on Facebook and, with 613,098 followers, the fifth largest nonprofit on Twitter. Plus, 1 in every 3 Americans either Likes us on Facebook or has a friend who does! We reach roughly 2.2 million young people every day, and we know what content keeps them coming back for more. We’ll help you to boost your social media rep through:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Social Media Audit</li>\r\n	<li>Training on Best Practices</li>\r\n	<li>Social Media Strategic Plan</li>\r\n	<li>Short Term Social Media Implementation (< 4 months)</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:4:\"icon\";s:14:\"user-interface\";s:10:\"customicon\";s:71:\"http://www.tmiagency.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Services_social.png\";}i:8;a:4:{s:5:\"title\";s:15:\"DATA & RESEARCH\";s:11:\"description\";s:689:\"<p>(5) Did you know young people are 18% more likely to volunteer if they are on a sports team? Or that 75.9% of young people whose friends regularly volunteer also volunteer, versus only 41.7% those whose friends don’t? We know A LOT about our audience—how much do you know about yours? We’ll use our in-house data analyst rockstars to bring you up to speed on how to be more data focused and improve your programs accordingly. Possible services include: </p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Data Collection & Analysis</li>\r\n	<li>Youth-Focused Quarterly Data Reports (Yearly Subscription)</li>\r\n	<li>Customized Research Reports</li>\r\n	<li>Creation & Maintenance of Youth Advisory Councils</li>\r\n</ul>\";s:4:\"icon\";s:14:\"user-interface\";s:10:\"customicon\";s:69:\"http://www.tmiagency.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/Services_data.png\";}s:12:\"_multiwidget\";i:1;}','yes'),(238,'widget_stag_section_team','a:2:{i:2;a:5:{s:5:\"title\";s:10:\"The Brains\";s:8:\"subtitle\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"color\";s:7:\"#ffffff\";s:2:\"bg\";s:7:\"#00d4ab\";s:4:\"link\";s:0:\"\";}s:12:\"_multiwidget\";i:1;}','yes'),(245,'fu_header_font','ProximaNova-Bold-webfont.ttf','yes'),(246,'fu_lists_font','Choose a font','yes'),(247,'fu_body_font','ProximaNova-Reg-webfont.ttf','yes'),(248,'fu_custom_one_font','ProximaNova-Light-webfont.ttf','yes'),(249,'fu_custom_one','#slideshow .slider-content h2','yes'),(250,'fu_custom_two_font','ProximaNova-Bold-webfont.ttf','yes'),(251,'fu_custom_two','#contact button','yes'),(252,'fu_custom_three_font','Choose a font','yes'),(253,'fu_custom_three','','yes'),(254,'fu_custom_four_font','Choose a font','yes'),(255,'fu_custom_four','','yes'),(256,'fu_custom_five_font','Choose a font','yes'),(257,'fu_custom_five','','yes'),(912,'auto_core_update_notified','a:4:{s:4:\"type\";s:7:\"success\";s:5:\"email\";s:19:\"admin@tmiagency.org\";s:7:\"version\";s:5:\"3.8.2\";s:9:\"timestamp\";i:1397027540;}','y